#: ../../../the_black_code_style/index.md:1
msgid "The Black Code Style"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/index.md:12
msgid "_Black_ is a PEP 8 compliant opinionated formatter with its own style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/index.md:14
msgid ""
"While keeping the style unchanged throughout releases has always been a "
"goal, the _Black_ code style isn't set in stone. It evolves to accommodate "
"for new features in the Python language and, occasionally, in response to "
"user feedback. Large-scale style preferences presented in {doc}"
"`current_style` are very unlikely to change, but minor style aspects and "
"details might change according to the stability policy presented below. "
"Ongoing style considerations are tracked on GitHub with the [style](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/labels/T%3A%20style) issue label."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/index.md:24
msgid "Stability Policy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/index.md:26
msgid ""
"The following policy applies for the _Black_ code style, in non pre-release "
"versions of _Black_:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/index.md:29
msgid ""
"If code has been formatted with _Black_, it will remain unchanged when "
"formatted with the same options using any other release in the same calendar "
"year."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/index.md:32
msgid ""
"This means projects can safely use `black ~= 26.0` without worrying about "
"formatting changes disrupting their project in 2026. We may still fix bugs "
"where _Black_ crashes on some code, and make other improvements that do not "
"affect formatting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/index.md:36
msgid ""
"In rare cases, we may make changes affecting code that has not been "
"previously formatted with _Black_. For example, we have had bugs where we "
"accidentally removed some comments. Such bugs can be fixed without breaking "
"the stability policy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/index.md:40
msgid ""
"The first release in a new calendar year _may_ contain formatting changes, "
"although these will be minimised as much as possible. This is to allow for "
"improved formatting enabled by newer Python language syntax as well as due "
"to improvements in the formatting logic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/index.md:45
msgid ""
"The `--preview` and `--unstable` flags are exempt from this policy. There "
"are no guarantees around the stability of the output with these flags passed "
"into _Black_. They are intended for allowing experimentation with proposed "
"changes to the _Black_ code style. The `--preview` style at the end of a "
"year should closely match the stable style for the next year, but we may "
"always make changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../the_black_code_style/index.md:51
msgid "Documentation for both the current and future styles can be found:"
msgstr ""

